text: Julieta Jankunas (born 20 January 1999) is an Argentine field hockey player and part of the Argentina national team. She participated in the 2014 Summer Youth Olympics, and the 2016 Women's Hockey Junior World Cup. She won a gold medal at the 2019 Pan American Games. On club level she plays for Universitario de Córdoba in Argentina.
